26
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,621
( Gon grunts )

27
00:02:01,655 --> 00:02:04,024
Killua: Ikalgo will take
the northeast elevator

28
00:02:04,057 --> 00:02:06,927
to the basement
to search for palm.

29
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:10,631
If you find her,
escape without us.

30
00:02:10,664 --> 00:02:11,932
Ikalgo: You got it.

31
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,568
Killua: If the king
and his three royal guards

32
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,570
are in the throne room
together when we get there,

33
00:02:16,603 --> 00:02:17,938
then we proceed with the plan.

34
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,606
But if they’re not there,

35
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,242
then i’m sure
it’s gonna be a problem.

36
00:02:21,275 --> 00:02:24,712
Gon: You’re really hung up
on that, aren’t you?

37
00:02:24,745 --> 00:02:26,714
Ikalgo:
Yeah, what are the chances?

38
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:28,582
It’s pretty unlikely.

39
00:02:28,615 --> 00:02:30,917
Killua: It is,
but you’ve gotta admit

40
00:02:30,951 --> 00:02:33,020
unlikely things
happen all the time.

41
00:02:33,053 --> 00:02:35,255
Ikalgo: Isn’t that
kind of a contradiction?

42
00:02:35,289 --> 00:02:37,725
Killua: We did
a bunch of research

43
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:38,959
on the enemy’s behavior

44
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:41,628
and used it
to decide when to attack.

45
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:43,697
When you think you know
exactly where and when

46
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:47,100
you can expect someone to be,
more often than not,

47
00:02:47,134 --> 00:02:49,670
that’s when
the unexpected happens.

48
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:52,239
It was pretty common
in my old job.

49
00:02:52,272 --> 00:02:54,574
Plan all you want,
but the unexpected

50
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:56,977
will always find a way
trip you up.

51
00:02:57,010 --> 00:03:00,947
It was easy to guarantee success
in that line of work.

52
00:03:00,981 --> 00:03:04,184
I could just wait
for the right moment.

53
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:06,120
We don’t have that luxury.

54
00:03:06,153 --> 00:03:10,024
As soon as we make a move,
there’s no turning back.

55
00:03:10,057 --> 00:03:13,928
Hesitate for one second,
and it can mean death.

56
00:03:13,961 --> 00:03:16,831
We need to plan
for every scenario

57
00:03:16,864 --> 00:03:19,133
and decide what we would do.

58
00:03:19,166 --> 00:03:20,300
♪

59
00:03:20,334 --> 00:03:22,803
They might not be
in the throne room,

60
00:03:22,836 --> 00:03:25,605
but if they’re still
in the palace, it’s okay.

61
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:27,908
Pitou’s en is enough
to cover the palace,

62
00:03:27,941 --> 00:03:31,745
the surrounding courtyards,
and then some,

63
00:03:31,778 --> 00:03:34,681
so as soon as we enter,
we need to see

64
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:37,685
if we can sense that creepy aura
anywhere close by.

65
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:40,955
That’ll tell us
whether or not they’re there.

66
00:03:40,988 --> 00:03:45,626
Then we just follow that aura to
where it feels the most dense.

67
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:47,961
They’ll be right at its center.

68
00:03:47,995 --> 00:03:52,633
But the question is what to do
if we don’t sense pitou’s aura,

69
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:55,969
because then it means
they’re not in the palace,

70
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:58,572
or it could mean
they are in the palace,

71
00:03:58,605 --> 00:04:00,140
but they’re not using en.

72
00:04:00,174 --> 00:04:01,609
Ikalgo: Would there
be a situation

73
00:04:01,642 --> 00:04:02,910
where they’d be in the palace,

74
00:04:02,943 --> 00:04:05,078
but not use their en
to guard the king?

75
00:04:05,112 --> 00:04:06,680
Gon: Yeah, like with Mr. Knov,

76
00:04:06,713 --> 00:04:08,882
that time when he
infiltrated the palace.

77
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,117
Ikalgo: Oh!

78
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,284
Killua: Right.

79
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:13,020
That’s what I can’t figure out.

80
00:04:13,053 --> 00:04:18,025
According to Colt, knov saw
a guy named pouf’s aura.

81
00:04:18,058 --> 00:04:21,795
The royal guard
never leaves the king’s side,

82
00:04:21,829 --> 00:04:24,765
so if pouf was there,
i’m positive the other two

83
00:04:24,798 --> 00:04:26,633
were in the palace
with the king, too.

84
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:30,738
But then why did pitou
stop using the puppets,

85
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,706
leave security to pouf,

86
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:36,142
and clear the stage
for knov to easily break in?

87
00:04:36,176 --> 00:04:39,746
Probably because of how
pitou’s ability seems to work.

88
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:43,651
Gon: Well, then we
should ask Colt himself.

89
00:04:43,684 --> 00:04:44,952
Killua: Yeah.

90
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:50,123
Colt: I’d guess pitou was giving
someone medical attention.

91
00:04:50,157 --> 00:04:51,558
Killua: What?

92
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:54,161
Colt: I did tell you
that pitou was the one

93
00:04:54,194 --> 00:04:56,763
who repaired kite, didn’t I?

94
00:04:56,797 --> 00:05:00,701
In hindsight, I don’t believe
pitou used en during that time.

95
00:05:00,734 --> 00:05:05,172
Healing must require
a great deal of concentration.

96
00:05:05,205 --> 00:05:07,908
I assume that
whenever healing someone,

97
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:11,111
pitou’s unable to use en
or the puppets.

98
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:13,913
Killua: Now it all makes sense.

99
00:05:13,947 --> 00:05:17,184
Someone got hurt
and needed healing.

100
00:05:17,217 --> 00:05:20,053
It was probably the king
or maybe one of the guards.

101
00:05:20,087 --> 00:05:22,856
That’s why the en
and the puppets disappeared.

102
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,225
Ikalgo: Wait. Hold on.

103
00:05:24,258 --> 00:05:26,761
As strong as those monsters are,

104
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:29,229
who would have had
the skills to injure them?

105
00:05:29,263 --> 00:05:30,798
Gon: Good question.

106
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,599
Killua: An internal dispute?

107
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:34,668
Gon: Maybe the king injured
one of the royal guards

108
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:35,869
for some reason?

109
00:05:35,903 --> 00:05:37,838
Ikalgo: No.
No, that’s impossible.

110
00:05:37,871 --> 00:05:40,707
Pitou would have to put
the king in extreme danger

111
00:05:40,741 --> 00:05:43,677
by removing the en so that they
could heal somebody else,

112
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:45,545
and that’s never gonna happen.

113
00:05:45,579 --> 00:05:47,714
I’m sure of it.

114
00:05:47,748 --> 00:05:49,883
Killua: Then the one
who was injured...

115
00:05:49,917 --> 00:05:52,253
( Gon gasps ) Was the king!

116
00:05:52,286 --> 00:05:53,888
♪

117
00:05:53,921 --> 00:05:56,724
Morel: I see.
It does make sense.

118
00:05:56,757 --> 00:05:58,959
But I guess
the bigger question now

119
00:05:58,992 --> 00:06:00,994
is who was it
that injured the king?

120
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:03,597
The royal guard
would never harm him,

121
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:05,932
and you could rule out
the underlings, too.

122
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:08,202
They’d never so much
as put a scratch on him.

123
00:06:08,235 --> 00:06:11,805
Gon: You’re right, and that’s
why we’re pretty sure...

124
00:06:12,940 --> 00:06:15,009
Morel: He injured himself?!

125
00:06:15,042 --> 00:06:17,211
Wait. How could that
have happened?

126
00:06:17,244 --> 00:06:19,780
Gon: We don’t know
what’s going on here yet,

127
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:20,981
but it’s all we’ve got.

128
00:06:21,014 --> 00:06:22,115
- ( Ikalgo grunts )
- Killua: Mm-hmm.

129
00:06:24,751 --> 00:06:26,753
Morel: I’ll admit it.

130
00:06:26,787 --> 00:06:30,257
I didn’t question our sudden
stroke of luck too much,

131
00:06:30,290 --> 00:06:32,592
but that chance
wouldn’t have been possible

132
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:34,728
under normal circumstances.

133
00:06:36,763 --> 00:06:39,933
Are they starting
to lose control?

134
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:42,136
Not good.

135
00:06:42,169 --> 00:06:45,839
I’m starting to think that
something’s going to go wrong.

136
00:06:46,974 --> 00:06:49,543
( Siren blares )

137
00:06:49,576 --> 00:06:52,746
Announcer: We will now begin
moving to the palace.

138
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:57,951
Citizens of sector a-1,
assemble in Diego Plaza at once.

139
00:06:59,253 --> 00:07:01,255
Citizens of the other sectors

140
00:07:01,288 --> 00:07:04,792
should prepare to move out next.

141
00:07:04,825 --> 00:07:06,894
♪

142
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:12,532
Knuckle: Well, here they come.

143
00:07:12,566 --> 00:07:15,202
Shoot: It looks like
their march has begun at last.

144
00:07:15,235 --> 00:07:19,039
Ten hours until midnight,
when the sorting starts.

145
00:07:21,074 --> 00:07:23,510
Menthuthuyoupi:
In just 25 hours,

146
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:25,746
tomorrow afternoon at 3:00,

147
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:29,149
five million humans
will fill the palace grounds.

148
00:07:29,183 --> 00:07:32,019
Any change in the capital?

149
00:07:32,052 --> 00:07:34,888
Neferpitou: Mm, I thought
it was just one skilled enemy,

150
00:07:34,922 --> 00:07:36,857
but there’s a bunch of ’em meow.

151
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:39,960
Shaiapouf: It seems
that they have backup.

152
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:42,229
Menthuthuyoupi: They may
try to use the celebration

153
00:07:42,262 --> 00:07:45,098
as a cover so they can get
as close as possible.

154
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:48,202
Neferpitou: So the biggest risk
will be during the sorting.

155
00:07:48,235 --> 00:07:50,771
Shaiapouf: Yes,
since the king himself

156
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:54,174
will be actively participating
in the sorting.

157
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:55,743
And because of that,

158
00:07:55,776 --> 00:07:58,646
our greatest concern
is that the king

159
00:07:58,679 --> 00:08:01,715
may somehow be spirited away
beyond our reach.

160
00:08:01,748 --> 00:08:04,851
Let’s just say that one of them

161
00:08:04,885 --> 00:08:07,654
has the ability
to teleport objects.

162
00:08:07,688 --> 00:08:09,757
Let’s further assume
that they use that ability

163
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:13,761
to isolate and teleport
the king somewhere far away,

164
00:08:13,794 --> 00:08:18,699
so at least one of us must stay
close by the king’s side

165
00:08:18,732 --> 00:08:21,068
and guard him
throughout the entire sorting.

166
00:08:21,101 --> 00:08:23,604
Menthuthuyoupi: He would
never allow us to do that.

167
00:08:23,637 --> 00:08:25,539
The king’s been
irritated enough with us

168
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:28,675
because of how close we’ve
been covering him as it is.

169
00:08:28,709 --> 00:08:31,078
Shaiapouf: Then we guard him
secretly without his knowledge.

170
00:08:31,111 --> 00:08:35,048
The only problem with that
is that we need someone

171
00:08:35,082 --> 00:08:37,618
close enough
to monitor his surroundings

172
00:08:37,651 --> 00:08:40,087
while he carries out
his role in the sorting...

173
00:08:41,655 --> 00:08:44,892
Someone whose size
won’t draw attention

174
00:08:44,925 --> 00:08:48,295
and who won’t get distracted
by an amusing task.

175
00:08:48,328 --> 00:08:50,697
Very well, then.

176
00:08:50,731 --> 00:08:53,667
Clearly the best choice
we have is me.

177
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:57,304
It is a mantle which I
will be quite proud to bear.

178
00:08:58,705 --> 00:08:59,706
Neferpitou: Hmm?

179
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:01,976
Shaiapouf: Is something wrong?

180
00:09:02,009 --> 00:09:03,978
Neferpitou: Meow all
of the enemy presences

181
00:09:04,011 --> 00:09:05,846
have completely disappeared...

182
00:09:07,181 --> 00:09:08,582
And I can’t sense

183
00:09:08,615 --> 00:09:11,084
any residual aura
from them whatsoever.

184
00:09:11,118 --> 00:09:15,756
They must be using zetsu to hide
amongst the marching humans.

185
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:17,791
♪

186
00:09:21,261 --> 00:09:23,497
Meleoron: Hey. What’s up?

187
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:25,899
Knuckle: There are
so many people.

188
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:29,236
Looks like they had
about a hundred per building.

189
00:09:29,269 --> 00:09:31,605
They all must have
been packed inside.

190
00:09:31,638 --> 00:09:34,141
Shoot: Then if we
all conceal our presences,

191
00:09:34,174 --> 00:09:36,276
they’ll be forced
to assume that we’re hiding

192
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:37,912
somewhere among the citizens.

193
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:39,780
Do you think there’s any chance

194
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:41,782
they’ll decide
to cancel the march altogether?

195
00:09:41,815 --> 00:09:43,016
Meleoron: No. No way.

196
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:45,753
That would mean delaying
or even canceling

197
00:09:45,786 --> 00:09:48,789
the entire celebration,
which would imply

198
00:09:48,822 --> 00:09:51,625
the king had accepted defeat
and compromised.

199
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:55,028
The royal guard’s
not gonna let that happen,

200
00:09:55,062 --> 00:09:58,799
so the celebration
is gonna begin as scheduled

201
00:09:58,832 --> 00:10:00,934
tomorrow at 3:00 P.M. sharp,

202
00:10:00,968 --> 00:10:04,138
and there’s not a damn thing
we can do to stop it.

203
00:10:05,172 --> 00:10:06,273
( Neferpitou sighs )

204
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:08,275
Once the humans started to move,

205
00:10:08,308 --> 00:10:12,045
my puppets couldn’t
tell them apart anymore.

206
00:10:12,079 --> 00:10:13,714
Well, what do you think?

207
00:10:13,747 --> 00:10:15,582
Should I recall them right meow?

208
00:10:15,616 --> 00:10:17,818
Shaiapouf: No.
Giving the enemy free rein

209
00:10:17,851 --> 00:10:19,653
would be simply ridiculous.

210
00:10:19,686 --> 00:10:21,221
A better strategy

211
00:10:21,255 --> 00:10:23,290
would be to have the puppets
join the soldiers

212
00:10:23,323 --> 00:10:26,193
that are guiding the citizens
as a deterrent.

213
00:10:27,361 --> 00:10:28,762
( Neferpitou groans )

214
00:10:42,943 --> 00:10:44,311
Knuckle: Hey.

215
00:10:44,344 --> 00:10:46,313
Morel: It’s just
like we thought.

216
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:49,349
The nen puppets
have joined the march.

217
00:10:49,383 --> 00:10:54,054
In another hour, those sectors
will be completely deserted.

218
00:10:57,291 --> 00:10:59,360
There are six entrances
to the hole

219
00:10:59,393 --> 00:11:02,062
that lead
straight to the palace.

220
00:11:02,095 --> 00:11:04,698
We’ll have to avoid
the front entrances

221
00:11:04,731 --> 00:11:06,266
due to heightened security

222
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:11,138
and wait by a, b, and c
behind the palace.

223
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:12,773
Shoot: Once we’re inside

224
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:14,841
and able to gain access
to the rooms,

225
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,744
the only available exit
will lead us

226
00:11:16,777 --> 00:11:18,779
directly through
the inside of the palace.

227
00:11:18,812 --> 00:11:20,881
Knuckle: So what?
Are you getting scared?

228
00:11:20,914 --> 00:11:22,282
Shoot: That’s absurd.

229
00:11:22,316 --> 00:11:24,285
I just don’t want
to be caught off guard, okay?

230
00:11:24,318 --> 00:11:27,555
Waiting by the entrances
for the right moment

231
00:11:27,588 --> 00:11:29,090
involves quite a lot of risk.

232
00:11:29,122 --> 00:11:32,192
But if we were to enter
the rooms too early,

233
00:11:32,226 --> 00:11:35,096
we wouldn’t be able to exit
until midnight.

234
00:11:35,128 --> 00:11:37,097
Meleoron: If that’s the case,
we won’t be able

235
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:39,699
to get our hands
on any useful new information.

236
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:42,302
We’d just be flying blind
and hoping for the best.

237
00:11:42,336 --> 00:11:45,005
Shoot: Oh, and we
can’t use our cell phones

238
00:11:45,038 --> 00:11:46,573
anywhere near the palace,

239
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:48,976
since the ants
can pick up on the signal.

240
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:50,711
Sitting in that room for hours

241
00:11:50,744 --> 00:11:53,714
is just about the most dangerous
thing that we could do.

242
00:11:53,747 --> 00:11:57,017
If the situation changed,
we would have no way of knowing.

243
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:59,786
Knuckle: But you were the one
who said it would be too risky

244
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:01,088
for us to wait
outside the palace.

245
00:12:01,121 --> 00:12:02,255
Shoot: Yes.

246
00:12:02,289 --> 00:12:04,057
Meleoron:
Based on what i’ve seen,

247
00:12:04,091 --> 00:12:06,660
you shouldn’t take
their security net too lightly.

248
00:12:06,693 --> 00:12:08,662
- Knov: I’ll handle it.
- Meleoron: Huh?

249
00:12:08,695 --> 00:12:10,063
♪

250
00:12:10,097 --> 00:12:11,699
Knov: I’m the only one among us

251
00:12:11,732 --> 00:12:15,069
who can enter and exit
these rooms whenever I please.

252
00:12:15,102 --> 00:12:17,972
I’ll keep you all informed.

253
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:21,775
For now, you should rest here.

254
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:23,576
Morel: You sure you’ll be okay?

255
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,278
Knov: I’m just keeping watch.

256
00:12:25,312 --> 00:12:28,115
I can’t imagine
that’ll be a problem.

257
00:12:28,148 --> 00:12:33,887
I’ll be close, but right outside
of pitou’s en range, so...

258
00:12:33,921 --> 00:12:35,256
Morel: Hmm.

259
00:12:35,289 --> 00:12:38,292
Still, be as careful
as possible.

260
00:12:39,826 --> 00:12:42,896
Pitou doesn’t use
a standard circular en.

261
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:46,167
It changes shape like an amoeba,
extending its range.

262
00:12:48,068 --> 00:12:50,003
That’s exactly
what kite ran into.

263
00:12:50,037 --> 00:12:53,240
Knov: Yeah, he probably
did that deliberately.

264
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:54,841
It’s a true fighter’s instinct

265
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:57,911
to want a real sense
of how strong his opponent is.

266
00:12:57,945 --> 00:13:02,183
Knov: And his instinct
led him to underestimate them.

267
00:13:02,216 --> 00:13:04,652
That was his downfall.

268
00:13:04,685 --> 00:13:08,522
Morel: That en can extend
out to two kilometers.

269
00:13:08,555 --> 00:13:10,957
Make sure you stay out of range.

270
00:13:10,991 --> 00:13:13,260
( Knov chuckles )
Don’t worry.

271
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:18,799
Not a single one of you can
strike fear in me like they do.

272
00:13:18,832 --> 00:13:20,567
I won’t take any risks...

273
00:13:21,835 --> 00:13:23,870
Ever again.

274
00:13:29,076 --> 00:13:31,912
( Officer on microphone )
We will now head to the palace.

275
00:13:31,945 --> 00:13:34,981
Any person who leaves their line
will be shot on sight!

276
00:13:35,015 --> 00:13:37,584
Move out!

277
00:13:48,996 --> 00:13:50,564
King: Pitou...

278
00:13:50,597 --> 00:13:55,268
You knew that komugi
was being attacked, did you not?

279
00:13:55,302 --> 00:13:58,772
Neferpitou: Yes. I was
monitoring the area with en.

280
00:13:58,805 --> 00:14:03,810
However, I saw no threat to you,
sire, so I ignored it.

281
00:14:03,844 --> 00:14:07,281
King: From this point on, you’ll
keep an eye on komugi as well

282
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:10,751
and deal
with any threats at once.

283
00:14:10,784 --> 00:14:13,120
Neferpitou: Yes, as you wish.

284
00:14:19,259 --> 00:14:21,261
♪

285
00:14:30,904 --> 00:14:32,706
Knov: Tens of thousands
of people

286
00:14:32,739 --> 00:14:35,842
are marching in a line,
heading toward the king...

287
00:14:36,944 --> 00:14:38,746
Just like ants.

288
00:14:38,779 --> 00:14:40,281
No, lemmings.

289
00:14:40,314 --> 00:14:43,117
A march of death.

290
00:14:43,150 --> 00:14:45,252
It will be dark
before much longer.

291
00:14:45,285 --> 00:14:49,356
About time for me
to call morel and the others.

292
00:14:51,358 --> 00:14:52,659
( Gasps )

293
00:14:54,194 --> 00:14:57,864
Wait a second. What is that?

294
00:15:02,536 --> 00:15:04,605
Wing scales?

295
00:15:04,638 --> 00:15:06,573
The breeze...

296
00:15:06,607 --> 00:15:09,176
It’s carrying
the scales of his wings

297
00:15:09,209 --> 00:15:10,610
towards the citizens.

298
00:15:10,644 --> 00:15:12,112
That means...

299
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,185
I thought so.

300
00:15:18,218 --> 00:15:23,156
Every one of them looks
completely vacant, dazed.

301
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:28,062
Those scales must have
a hypnotic effect.

302
00:15:30,097 --> 00:15:32,666
Soldier: Stay in line
as you advance!

303
00:15:32,699 --> 00:15:34,701
Soldier #2:
Do not leave this line!

304
00:15:34,735 --> 00:15:36,870
Soldier #3:
Once you’re in position,

305
00:15:36,904 --> 00:15:39,206
wait for orders, and don’t move!

306
00:15:40,607 --> 00:15:42,642
Knov: Simple orders
repeated on a loop

307
00:15:42,676 --> 00:15:44,778
while tanks roll
in the background

308
00:15:44,811 --> 00:15:47,113
can easily seep into a mind

309
00:15:47,147 --> 00:15:50,217
exhausted from hours
of marching,

310
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:54,221
the perfect recipe
for hypnotic suggestion.

311
00:15:55,756 --> 00:15:57,291
Once the sorting begins

312
00:15:57,324 --> 00:15:59,726
and the blood starts to flow,

313
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:02,162
they will continue
to stand in place,

314
00:16:02,196 --> 00:16:05,966
obedient ’til the end,
when it’s their turn.

315
00:16:07,668 --> 00:16:09,603
( Knuckle snoring )

316
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:12,038
Morel: Hypnosis? I see.

317
00:16:12,072 --> 00:16:14,775
As long as they’re hypnotized,

318
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:16,877
the citizens won’t try to run,

319
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,945
but this works out for us.

320
00:16:18,979 --> 00:16:21,048
- Meleoron: Huh?
- Morel: We won’t have to worry

321
00:16:21,081 --> 00:16:23,016
about the whole crowd
flying into a total panic

322
00:16:23,050 --> 00:16:24,885
if the battle
starts to get out of control.

323
00:16:24,918 --> 00:16:26,553
Meleoron: Ah.

324
00:16:26,587 --> 00:16:29,190
Morel: So there won’t be
a massive stampede of people

325
00:16:29,223 --> 00:16:31,859
falling all over each other
to escape.

326
00:16:31,892 --> 00:16:33,794
This is a really big deal.

327
00:16:33,827 --> 00:16:36,863
Knuckle: And assuming
that over half of the people

328
00:16:36,897 --> 00:16:38,298
will be in place at midnight

329
00:16:38,332 --> 00:16:40,568
waiting for the sorting process
to get started,

330
00:16:40,601 --> 00:16:43,771
I would have expected a stampede

331
00:16:43,804 --> 00:16:46,573
to leave tens of thousands
of casualties.

332
00:16:46,607 --> 00:16:49,276
Morel: That’s the biggest thing
we were worried about.

333
00:16:49,309 --> 00:16:52,112
Now we can fight all we want.

334
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:55,082
Shoot: Six hours to go.

335
00:16:58,852 --> 00:17:00,220
Morel: Everyone’s here.

336
00:17:00,254 --> 00:17:03,124
Gon: Have you guys
heard from palm yet?

337
00:17:03,156 --> 00:17:04,157
Morel: No.

338
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:07,761
Gon: I see.

339
00:17:07,794 --> 00:17:10,997
Morel: We’ll wait ’til
half an hour before go time.

340
00:17:11,031 --> 00:17:13,233
I just wish we knew
what was inside of there.

341
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,769
That could change things.

342
00:17:14,801 --> 00:17:16,970
( Gon grunts )

343
00:17:17,004 --> 00:17:20,241
( Shoot thinking )
They both look so calm,

344
00:17:20,274 --> 00:17:22,610
killua in particular.

345
00:17:22,643 --> 00:17:24,278
He shows
none of the vulnerability

346
00:17:24,311 --> 00:17:25,979
he displayed when we fought.

347
00:17:26,013 --> 00:17:29,016
It’s like he’s
overflowing with confidence.

348
00:17:29,049 --> 00:17:31,985
But I can’t help but wonder,

349
00:17:32,019 --> 00:17:36,290
why is it that,
now and then, he seems so sad?

350
00:17:38,025 --> 00:17:41,695
No. I can’t worry
about others right now.

351
00:17:41,728 --> 00:17:43,230
Out of everyone here,

352
00:17:43,263 --> 00:17:46,700
i’m the one suffering
from the most anxiety.

353
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:50,971
The fate of humanity
rests on my shoulders.

354
00:17:52,239 --> 00:17:54,108
Knuckle: Colt is a good guy.

355
00:17:54,141 --> 00:17:58,712
Meleoron and ikalgo,
they both have good hearts.

356
00:17:58,745 --> 00:18:02,148
It doesn’t matter
if they’re humans or ants.

357
00:18:02,182 --> 00:18:03,984
Everyone has a heart.

358
00:18:04,017 --> 00:18:06,152
That has to be true.

359
00:18:06,186 --> 00:18:09,156
Let’s hope
the king has one, too.

360
00:18:09,189 --> 00:18:14,161
Even so, some of them
are going to have to die.

361
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,964
It’s us or them.

362
00:18:17,998 --> 00:18:20,534
Gon: It’s almost time, kite.

363
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:22,769
I promise,
no matter what it takes,

364
00:18:22,803 --> 00:18:25,172
i’ll get you back
to the way you used to be...

365
00:18:27,274 --> 00:18:29,610
By defeating that ant.

366
00:18:30,811 --> 00:18:32,846
Killua: He’s fired up.

367
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:35,049
I’ll focus
on providing support

368
00:18:35,082 --> 00:18:38,619
so that no one else
can interfere in his battle,

369
00:18:38,652 --> 00:18:43,023
using my new move, godspeed.

370
00:18:43,056 --> 00:18:45,725
Morel: I feel so tired.

371
00:18:45,759 --> 00:18:48,528
All these battles
are taking their toll.

372
00:18:48,562 --> 00:18:50,864
On a scale of one to 100,

373
00:18:50,898 --> 00:18:52,099
i’m about a 40.

374
00:18:52,132 --> 00:18:54,134
No, 35.

375
00:18:55,736 --> 00:18:57,538
Can’t cry about it now.

376
00:18:57,571 --> 00:19:01,141
With knov out,
i’m the only one left.

377
00:19:01,175 --> 00:19:04,679
I’d hoped to fight
at full strength,

378
00:19:04,711 --> 00:19:08,882
but it’s much easier
to accept my fate this way.

379
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:11,552
I’ll focus on playing the decoy

380
00:19:11,585 --> 00:19:14,688
and drawing my target
away from the king.

381
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:20,727
Knov: I’m sorry,
morel, everyone,

382
00:19:20,761 --> 00:19:22,896
( shudders ) But i--

383
00:19:22,930 --> 00:19:24,965
I can’t face them again.

384
00:19:26,066 --> 00:19:28,201
I’ll go check on the palace.

385
00:19:32,005 --> 00:19:35,842
( Meleoron inhales )

386
00:19:35,876 --> 00:19:37,878
So two minutes
is about the longest

387
00:19:37,911 --> 00:19:39,079
I can hold my breath.

388
00:19:39,112 --> 00:19:41,681
Given how tense i’ll be,

389
00:19:41,715 --> 00:19:44,885
my limit will probably
be half that at best.

390
00:19:44,918 --> 00:19:46,787
It’s fine.

391
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:48,689
A minute is
more than enough time.

392
00:19:51,091 --> 00:19:54,094
Ikalgo: Tomorrow at midnight,

393
00:19:54,127 --> 00:19:56,229
I will be reborn.

394
00:19:56,263 --> 00:19:59,299
I couldn’t have dreamed
of this life a few days ago.

395
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:02,303
Thank you for that, killua.

396
00:20:02,336 --> 00:20:07,942
I promise to carry out
my mission for you.

397
00:20:07,975 --> 00:20:09,310
Tomorrow...

398
00:20:09,343 --> 00:20:12,179
Will be my birthday.

399
00:20:29,296 --> 00:20:31,932
King: I am king...

400
00:20:34,368 --> 00:20:37,238
But who am I, really?

401
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:44,044
I wonder,
for what reason was I born?

402
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:50,050
Morel: Our time’s up.

403
00:20:50,083 --> 00:20:51,051
Let’s go!

404
00:20:51,084 --> 00:20:52,852
♪

405
00:21:07,768 --> 00:21:09,203
Gon: Palm.

406
00:21:19,847 --> 00:21:24,819
Narrator: Ten minutes remain
until they enter the palace.

407
00:21:24,852 --> 00:21:25,820
♪

408
00:21:25,853 --> 00:21:27,855
( Singing in Japanese )

